> **Google Cloud Console Setup**: You will need to enable the **Gmail API** in your existing Google Cloud project (the one with ClientId `13080223109-...`) and add the `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly` scope. This requires Google's **verification process** since it's a sensitive/restricted scope — plan for ~1-2 weeks of review.

> [!WARNING]
> **UPI on iOS**: Apple **prohibits** third-party apps from reading SMS. There is **no workaround**. The only compliant cross-platform solution for UPI tracking is the **RBI Account Aggregator (AA) framework** or manual entry. See the detailed analysis in [Section 5](#5-upi-transaction-tracking-strategy).

> [!CAUTION]
> **Data Sensitivity**: Storing and processing raw email content containing financial data has regulatory implications. All email content must be processed in-memory and never persisted as raw text. Only the extracted, structured transaction data should be stored.

